def str_to_list(s):
    try:
        s.split(',')
        return [m['genre_title'] for m in l]
    except ValueError as e:
        return []
    
def s_zfill(i):
    # zfill prepends 0 to the string
    return str(i).zfill(6)+'.mp3'
    
def copy_file_path(fp):
    pwd_path=!pwd
    pwd_path = pwd_path[0]
    src = pwd_path+'/fma_small/'+fp
    dst = pwd_path+'/warmup/'+fp
    copyfile(src, dst)
    return 'File Copy: Success'

                  & (tracks_df['split'] == 'training')].groupby('genre_top').count()['track_id'])

# subsets the data to just hip-hop and folk test_set
test_set_tracks_df = tracks_df[(tracks_df['subset'] == 'small')\
                         & (tracks_df['genre_top'].isin(['Folk','Hip-Hop']))
                         & (tracks_df['split'] == 'test')]
test_set_tracks_df = test_set_tracks_df.groupby('genre_top').apply(lambda s: s.sample(25, random_state=42))
test_set_tracks_df.index = test_set_tracks_df.index.droplevel()
test_set_tracks_df['file'] = test_set_tracks_df.track_id.apply(s_zfill)

# subsets the data to just hip-hop and folk
sm_tracks_df = tracks_df[(tracks_df['subset'] == 'small')\
                         & (tracks_df['genre_top'].isin(['Folk','Hip-Hop']))
                         & (tracks_df['split'] == 'training')]
sm_tracks_df = sm_tracks_df.groupby('genre_top').apply(lambda s: s.sample(250, random_state=42))
sm_tracks_df.index = sm_tracks_df.index.droplevel()
sm_tracks_df['file'] = sm_tracks_df.track_id.apply(s_zfill)

def show_feature(feature):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,4))
    a=merged_features_df[feature][merged_features_df['genre_top']=='Folk'].apply(float)
    b=merged_features_df[feature][merged_features_df['genre_top']=='Hip-Hop'].apply(float)
    plt.title(feature)
    sns.distplot(a)
    sns.distplot(b)
    plt.show()

stoptokens = set(stopwords.words('english'))
[stoptokens.add(i) for i in ['&','de','various','/','+','-','la','les','los','el','le','artists','band','&amp']];
name_popularity = ' '.join([str(i).lower() for i in albums_df['artist_name'].unique()]).split(' ')
name_popularity = [i for i in name_popularity if i not in stoptokens]
wordcloud = WordCloud(background_color="white", width=1000, height=1000).generate(' '.join(name_popularity))
name_popularity = Counter(name_popularity)
total = name_popularity.most_common(1000)
display(pd.DataFrame(total, columns=['name','count']).head(3))
plt.figure(figsize=(15,15))
plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation="bilinear")
plt.axis("off")
plt.savefig('bandnames.png')
plt.show()
